Package: yaamake
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, yaamake-makefiles
Recommends: yaamake-teensy
Suggests: git
Description: Makefile system to build and program AVR projects
 Yaamake is handy makefile system to be used with gnu make
 for building and programming AVR projects. IT allows you to
 write simple Makefile with few variable definitions and
 upplies lot of defined targets (actions).
 .
 Yaamake is mainly used by Yaal project, but it's also
 very useful separately.
 .
 This package contains tool to find location of actual makefiles.

Package: yaamake-doc
Architecture: all
Description: documentation for yaamake
 <insert long description, indented with spaces>

Package: yaamake-makefiles1
Architecture: all
Provides: yaamake-makefiles
Depends: make
Description: Actual makefiles for yaamake
 This package contains one version of yaamake's makefile system.
 You can have multiple different versions of these installed.
 Command yaamake is used to return path to one of these makefiles.

Package: yaamake-teensy
Architecture: any
Description: Teensy programmer used by yaamake
 This package contains teensy_loader_cli used to program teensy boards.

